he ruler/subject relationship and a guide for the public performance of an enlightened ruler. Wang Bi's work initiated the reading of the Laozi, the Book of Changes and the Analects as philosophical texts and has had a lasting impact on Chinese philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMetaphysics. 0aPhilosophy, Chinesey221 B.C.-960 A.D. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 7aRELIGION / Taoism (see also PHILOSOPHY / Taoist).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079148886740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791488867423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791488867/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles